Mission: (f990) GUTHRIE CORTLAND MEDICAL CENTER, INC., LOCATED IN CORTLAND, NY, IS A NOT-FOR-PROFIT ACUTE CARE HOSPITAL. THE HOSPITAL PROVIDES GENERAL INPATIENT, INPATIENT PSYCHIATRIC, OUTPATIENT, EMERGENCY, LONG-TERM HOME HEALTHCARE AND SKILLED NURSING SERVICES TO ITS RESIDENTS IN THE GREATER CORTLAND COUNTY AREA.(f990) GUTHRIE CORLTAND MEDICAL CENTER IS DEDICATED TO SERVING THE LIFELONG HEALTH CARE NEEDS OF CORTLAND AND THE SURROUNDING AREA. AS A TEAM-ORIENTED COMMUNITY HEALTH AND MEDICAL ORGANIZATION, GUTHRIE CORTLAND MEDICAL CENTER PROVIDES QUALITY CARE, SKILL AND COMPASSION TO ALL PEOPLE REGARDLESS OF THEIR ABILITY TO PAY. OUR HOSPITAL IS COMMITTED TO: - IMPROVING THE WELLNESS OF THE COMMUNITY THROUGH LEADERSHIP IN HEALTH-RELATED ACTIVITIES AND EDUCATION. - SUPPORTING AND PRESERVING THE PERSONAL AND PROFESSIONAL GROWTH OF OUR QUALITY HEALTH-CARE TEAM, THEREBY PROVIDING STIMULATING ENVIRONMENT FOR ALL EMPLOYEES. - RECRUITING AND RETAINING QUALITY HEALTHCARE PROFESSIONALS. - COOPERATING WITH OTHER HEALTHCARE PROVIDERS,REGULATORY AGENCIES, AND INSURANCE COMPANIES TO ADVANCE OUR SERVICE TO EVERY MEMBER OF THE COMMUNITY. - MAINTAINING THE HOSPITALS FINANCIAL VIABILITY FOR THE WELL-BEING OF THE COMMUNITY. - ACQUIRING AND MAINTAINING EQUIPMENT REQUIRED TO PROVIDE QUALITY CARE. - ENCOURAGING THE ACTIVE PARTICIPATION OF COMMUNITY MEMBERS IN A VOLUNTEER CAPACITY IN ORDER TO AUGMENT OUR SERVICES. GUTHRIE CORTLAND MEDICAL CENTER IS A VOLUNTARY, NOT-FOR-PROFIT CORPORATION. THE MEDICAL CENTER PROVIDES HEALTH CARE SERVICES OF PREVENTIVE, CURATIVE AND EDUCATIONAL NATURE. THE PRIMARY SERVICES PROVIDED ARE: ACUTE MEDICAL INPATIENT CARE (INCLUDING MATERNITY), PSYCHIATRIC INPATIENT CARE, RESIDENTIAL CARE (SKILLED NURSING FACILITY), EMERGENCY ROOM, AMBULATORY SURGERY, OUTPATIENT DIAGNOSTIC SERVICES, LONG TERM HOME HEALTH CARE PROGRAM, COMMUNITY HEALTH WELLNESS SCREENING, ADULT DAY CARE AND CLINIC.

ActivityOrMissionDesc: GUTHRIE CORTLAND MEDICAL CENTER PROVIDES QUALITY HEALTHCARE WITH SKILL & COMPASSION, MEETING THE LIFELONG NEEDS OF ALL CITIZENS OF CORTLAND & THE SURROUNDING COMMUNITY.
MissionDesc: GUTHRIE CORTLAND MEDICAL CENTER, INC., LOCATED IN CORTLAND, NY, IS A NOT-FOR-PROFIT ACUTE CARE HOSPITAL. THE HOSPITAL PROVIDES GENERAL INPATIENT, INPATIENT PSYCHIATRIC, OUTPATIENT, EMERGENCY, LONG-TERM HOME HEALTHCARE AND SKILLED NURSING SERVICES TO ITS RESIDENTS IN THE GREATER CORTLAND COUNTY AREA.
Desc: GUTHRIE CORLTAND MEDICAL CENTER IS DEDICATED TO SERVING THE LIFELONG HEALTH CARE NEEDS OF CORTLAND AND THE SURROUNDING AREA. AS A TEAM-ORIENTED COMMUNITY HEALTH AND MEDICAL ORGANIZATION, GUTHRIE CORTLAND MEDICAL CENTER PROVIDES QUALITY CARE, SKILL AND COMPASSION TO ALL PEOPLE REGARDLESS OF THEIR ABILITY TO PAY. OUR HOSPITAL IS COMMITTED TO: - IMPROVING THE WELLNESS OF THE COMMUNITY THROUGH LEADERSHIP IN HEALTH-RELATED ACTIVITIES AND EDUCATION. - SUPPORTING AND PRESERVING THE PERSONAL AND PROFESSIONAL GROWTH OF OUR QUALITY HEALTH-CARE TEAM, THEREBY PROVIDING STIMULATING ENVIRONMENT FOR ALL EMPLOYEES. - RECRUITING AND RETAINING QUALITY HEALTHCARE PROFESSIONALS. - COOPERATING WITH OTHER HEALTHCARE PROVIDERS,REGULATORY AGENCIES, AND INSURANCE COMPANIES TO ADVANCE OUR SERVICE TO EVERY MEMBER OF THE COMMUNITY. - MAINTAINING THE HOSPITALS FINANCIAL VIABILITY FOR THE WELL-BEING OF THE COMMUNITY. - ACQUIRING AND MAINTAINING EQUIPMENT REQUIRED TO PROVIDE QUALITY CARE. - ENCOURAGING THE ACTIVE PARTICIPATION OF COMMUNITY MEMBERS IN A VOLUNTEER CAPACITY IN ORDER TO AUGMENT OUR SERVICES. GUTHRIE CORTLAND MEDICAL CENTER IS A VOLUNTARY, NOT-FOR-PROFIT CORPORATION. THE MEDICAL CENTER PROVIDES HEALTH CARE SERVICES OF PREVENTIVE, CURATIVE AND EDUCATIONAL NATURE. THE PRIMARY SERVICES PROVIDED ARE: ACUTE MEDICAL INPATIENT CARE (INCLUDING MATERNITY), PSYCHIATRIC INPATIENT CARE, RESIDENTIAL CARE (SKILLED NURSING FACILITY), EMERGENCY ROOM, AMBULATORY SURGERY, OUTPATIENT DIAGNOSTIC SERVICES, LONG TERM HOME HEALTH CARE PROGRAM, COMMUNITY HEALTH WELLNESS SCREENING, ADULT DAY CARE AND CLINIC.

Mission: (f990) THE MISSION AND PURPOSE OF THE YMCA IS TO SERVE THE COMMUNITY BY REACHING OUT TO EVERYONE IN THE COMMUNITY IN A SPIRIT OF INCLUSION AND FELLOWSHIP. YMCAS PUT CHRISTIAN PRINCIPLES INTO PRACTICE THROUGH PROGRAMS THAT BUILD HEALTHY SPIRIT, MIND, AND BODY FOR ALL. YMCA PROGRAMS FOCUS ON FOUR CORE VALUES - CARING, HONESTY, RESPECT, AND RESPONSIBILITY. WE SERVE MEN, WOMEN AND CHILDREN OF ALL AGES, RACES, ABILITIES, INCOMES, NATIONAL ORIGINS, AND RELIGIONS. WE PROVIDE FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE TO THOSE WHO NEED IT. WE IDENTIFY NEEDS WITHIN OUR COMMUNITY AND RESPOND TO THEM SO THAT THE ENTIRE COMMUNITY BENEFITS FROM OUR EFFORTS.THE ANNUAL SCHOLARSHIP PROGRAM APPROVED 84 YOUTH AND FAMILY MEMBERSHIP ASSISTANCE REQUESTS VALUED AT $18,588 INCLUDING FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE FOR AFTERSCHOOL, DAY CAMP AND OTHER YOUTH PROGRAMS.(f990) THE YMCA'S CHILDCARE PROGRAMS INCLUDE DROPIN CHILDCARE, UNIVERSAL PREKINDERGARTEN, WRAPAROUND AND JR. CAMP ADVENTURE. THESE PROGRAMS OFFER EXPERIENTIAL AND HANDS-ON LEARNING ACTIVITIES THAT PROVIDE CHALLENGE AND PROMOTE SPIRITUAL AWARENESS, MENTAL DEVELOPMENT, PHYSICAL WELL-BEING, SOCIAL GROWTH, AND SELF-RESPECT. IN A NURTURING AND STIMULATING ENVIRONMENT, CHILDREN DEVELOP THEIR PHYSICAL AND MENTAL CAPABILITIES, RECOGNIZE THE VALUE OF COOPERATION AND GAIN CONFIDENCE.
